AAUUTTHHOORR
       Nikos Drakos,  Computer Based Learning Unit, University of Leeds
       <nikos@cbl.leeds.ac.uk>. Several people have contributed suggestions,
       ideas, solutions, support and encouragement.

       The ppssttooiimmgg script was written by Marek Rouchal
       <marek@saftsack.fs.uni-bayreuth.de> as a generalisation of the ppssttooggiiff
       utility to allow graphic formats other than GIF to be created. Various
       options and enhancements have been added by Ross Moore.  Some of the
       code is based upon the pstoppm.ps postscript program originally written
       by Phillip Conrad (Perfect Byte, Inc.)  and modified by L. Peter
       Deutsch (Aladdin Enterprises).

